main event: A bright, disc-shaped object was reported hovering over Donnybrook, North Dakota on August 6, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as 30 feet in diameter, with a dome-shaped top and a bright, metallic appearance.
The object hovered silently for several minutes before accelerating rapidly and disappearing from view.
Investigations revealed no physical evidence at the scene, and interviews with additional witnesses failed to corroborate the sighting.
No radar contacts were reported in the vicinity at the time of the incident.
A separate sighting was reported by a witness driving near Donnybrook on the night of August 5, 1966, who observed a bright, circular object hovering and maneuvering at a high rate of speed.
witnesses: multiple witnesses, including Mrs. Anna Wilks and Mr. James Gilliard
photographs: yes, the report includes photographs of the site
